    <subfield code="y">00000 The redshift drift effect (\ref{delzomega}) for 15 year period of observations for various values of the varying speed of light parameter $n$. Negative $n$ correponds to $\dot{c} &amp;lt; 0$. The error bars are taken from Ref. \cite{Quercellini12} and presumably show that for $|n| &amp;lt; 0.045$ one cannot distinguish between VSL models and $\Lambda$CDM models. Larger positive values of $n$ (growing $c(t)$) make VSL model to become more like Cold Dark Matter (CDM) dust model.</subfield>
